  "diary": "Woke early to tend the basil and tomatoes—they're coming in nicely this year, and there's something grounding about watering them in that quiet morning light. The transit strike meant dropping extra cash on a rideshare to get to Interbay, which stung a bit, but the hospital was slammed anyway. The usual Thursday chaos: a couple of cardiac scares, a kid with a badly sprained ankle, the steady hum of beeping monitors and urgent voices. Grabbed a sandwich around eleven and tried to decompress for twenty minutes. By the time the Light Rail came back online at four, I was ready to head home. The rooftop felt like a sanctuary—deadheaded some spent blooms and checked the tomatoes again. Made a simple pasta with fresh basil for dinner, nothing fancy. Spent the evening with some Coltrane and an old novel, letting the day settle out of my bones.",
